canlogger (0.1.6-1) UNRELEASED; urgency=medium

  * README: correct the "building the package" section. Previous text implied
    macOS could build Debian packages natively, which it cannot. New text
    lists the three real options (build on Pi, build in Docker on Mac, build
    on any Debian/Ubuntu box) in order of least friction. Also updates the
    install example filenames to current version, and includes pandoc in the
    apt-install line for build dependencies.

 -- goatrnet <ian@openassistivetech.org>  Fri, 03 Jul 2026 23:20:00 +0000

canlogger (0.1.5-1) UNRELEASED; urgency=medium

  * Ship /usr/share/doc/canlogger/README.md uncompressed. It's small enough
    that gzipping just makes reading it slightly more annoying (zless/zcat
    every time). Man page updated to reference the uncompressed path.

 -- goatrnet <ian@openassistivetech.org>  Fri, 03 Jul 2026 23:00:00 +0000

canlogger (0.1.4-1) UNRELEASED; urgency=medium

  * Uploader: replace single-phase rclone move with two-phase copy + age-gated
    delete. Local segments now persist at least CANLOG_LOCAL_RETAIN (default
    14 days) after upload, giving users a grace period to work with fresh
    files in place. Local files that never uploaded successfully are never
    deleted regardless of age -- prune-safety is verified per-file via
    rclone check before any deletion.
  * Add canlogger(7) man page pointing at /usr/share/doc/canlogger/ for the
    full documentation. Sourced from markdown, generated with pandoc at
    build time; adds pandoc to Build-Depends.
  * README: document the manual-trigger command
    (systemctl start canlog-upload.service).

 -- goatrnet <ian@openassistivetech.org>  Fri, 03 Jul 2026 22:45:00 +0000

