canlogger (0.1.2-1) UNRELEASED; urgency=medium

  * Rename installed binaries to drop language-revealing extensions:
    canlog-rotate.py -> canlog-rotate, canlog-upload.sh -> canlog-upload.
    Per Debian policy, scripts in /usr/bin should not expose their
    implementation language in the filename.
  * Set a real maintainer email.

 -- goatrnet <ian@openassistivetech.org>  Thu, 18 Jun 2026 19:00:00 +0000

canlogger (0.1.1-1) UNRELEASED; urgency=medium

  * Install scripts into /usr/bin instead of /usr/local/bin, complying with
    Debian policy (/usr/local is reserved for the local administrator).
    Removes the dh_usrlocal override from debian/rules.

 -- goatrnet <ian@openassistivetech.org>  Thu, 18 Jun 2026 18:40:00 +0000

canlogger (0.1.0-1) UNRELEASED; urgency=medium

  * Initial packaging of the goatrnet CAN logger pipeline.
  * Includes canlog-rotate.py (capture + session-aware rotation),
    canlog-upload.sh (rclone-based spool drainer), and their systemd
    service/timer units.
  * canlogger.service is enabled automatically on install.
  * canlog-upload.timer is installed but NOT enabled, because rclone needs
    configuring with a remote first. See README.

 -- goatrnet <ian@openassistivetech.org>  Thu, 18 Jun 2026 12:00:00 +0000
